v(t) =  α(t) ⋅ v_0 + (1 - α(t)) ⋅ g ⋅ µ = α(t) ⋅ (v_0 - g ⋅ µ) + g ⋅ µ
a(t) = g ⋅ µ - v(t) = -α(t) ⋅ (v_0 - g ⋅ µ)
p(t) = p_0 + ( v_0 - g ⋅ µ ) ⋅ (α(t)-1) + (t_0 - t) ⋅ g ⋅ µ  
où v(t) est la vitesse du plongeur, p(t) sa profondeur, a(t) son accélération, et p_0, v_0 et t_0 correspondent aux conditions
initialies (profondeur, vitesse et temps).
